arts.ttl: The lowdown on West Brom 0 Millwall 0 - Lions grind out a point with a defensive masterclass
arts.sum: I’m sure it was a hard watch for the travelling Millwall fans who had to watch their team spend long spells without the ball but defend very well to earn their ninth point of the Championship season. Millwall bounced back from their 1-0 defeat at Cardiff on Tuesday to claim a point at West Brom in a 0-0 stalemate at The Hawthorns.

arts.ttl: Carlos Corberan demands more from West Brom as Millwall squander chances in stalemate
arts.sum: West Brom head coach Carlos Corberan has conceded that his side must up their game in creating and converting chances following a goalless draw with Millwall. Corberan expressed his thoughts on the performance: "We tried our best with lots of commitment but we need to find a way to score a goal," he said.

arts.ttl: Millwall boss Harris felt his team executed gameplan “superbly” in stalemate at West Bromwich
arts.sum: Neil Harris felt Millwall executed his game plan perfectly as they left West Brom with a point and a clean sheet despite having just 21 per cent possession. “My keeper didn’t have a save to make in the second half and we had three or four really good chances.”

Albion's Kyle Bartley and Maja sent weak shots straight to Millwall goalkeeper Lukas Jensen as they sought an opening. Millwall missed a golden opportunity to take the lead when Azeez failed to connect with Macaulay Langstaff’s cross at close range.

arts.ttl: West Brom’s woes in front of goal continue after draw with Millwall
arts.sum: Top scorer Josh Maja squandered their best opportunity.

arts.sum: West Brom have found Millwall a tough team to beat in recent seasons and Steve Davies foresees more frustration for the Black Country club at the Hawthorns on Saturday.

arts.ttl: Millwall boss Harris: Jed Wallace’s fight for game time underlines West Brom’s wealth of attacking options
arts.sum: Millwall head coach Neil Harris reckons Jed Wallace’s battle for minutes at West Brom this season underlines the strength in depth of their opponents on Saturday. Former Den favourite Wallace, 30, had not started a fixture for the Baggies this season – despite being their club captain – before their 1-0 home defeat to Middlesbrough on Tuesday night.
